# Subagent Markdown File Prefix Rule

When any subagent creates a `.md` document, the filename must start with a role prefix.

## Allowed Prefixes by Role

- `architect` -> `[架构]`
- `dev` -> `[研发]`
- `qa` -> `[QA]`
- `pm` -> `[产品]`
- `ued` -> `[交互]`
- `manager` -> `[主持人]` / `[项目经理]` / `[TODO经理]`（按 skill 选用，见下）

### Manager Skill 前缀映射

`manager` 子代理按当前 skill 选用对应前缀（保留旧前缀字面量，便于按主题识别）：

- skill `review-meeting` -> `[主持人]`
- skill `version-planning` -> `[项目经理]`
- skill `todo-drive` -> `[TODO经理]`

## Naming Requirement

- Use exactly one of the prefixes above at the beginning of the markdown filename.
- Keep the rest of the filename descriptive.
- If the subagent role is not listed above, do not create the `.md` file yet; ask for a prefix decision first.

## Fallback Rule for Unmapped Roles

- Unknown role -> block markdown creation until the user confirms which allowed prefix to use.
- Never invent a new prefix automatically.

## Examples

- `[架构]缓存分层设计.md`
- `[研发]账单导出修复方案.md`
- `[QA]回归测试清单.md`
